RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSING PENNY broke alertly and established the early advantage, set moderate fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, showed the way to the quarter marker, was set down in upper stretch, held foes at bay to the furlong grounds and drew clear in the final sixteenth. BIG JOLT raced four wide into the first turn, took back off of the moderate pace, slipped to the two path nearing the top of the lane, advanced at mid-stretch, was outkicked by the winner in the final stages and just held for second at the finish. BEA MISCHIEF was off a step slowly at the start, settled off of the moderate pace, went three wide into the far turn, was roused five wide into the stretch, rallied nearing the furlong pole, could not match strides with the winner in deep stretch and just missed for second, while clear in the end for third. PEACEHAVEN stalked the pace along the first turn, was well placed through the backstretch run and into the far turn, raced three wide into the stretch, came in tight and steadied slightly at mid-stretch and weakened in the final sixteenth. DARK INTENT raced close to the early pace, was a bit keen along the first turn and into the backstretch run, prompted the moderate pace to the second turn, lost position in upper stretch and gave way in the drive. BOSSY PEGASUS stalked the early pace while three deep on the first turn, maintained position through the backstretch run, raced three wide into the far turn, came four wide into the stretch and tired in the late going.

ENTRY.NAME: Missing Penny
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well,pace,well handled,drew clear late,held sway

ENTRY.NAME: Dark Intent
ENTRY.OWNER: Coleman Stacey Hogue Jennifer and Hooper Chris

ENTRY.NAME: Bea Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,5wide into stretch,outfinished,just missed 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Big Jolt
ENTRY.OWNER: Landeros David and Landeros Jorge T

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 72. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM'S STYLE was allowed to settle in the early running, raced two wide into the turn, was roused nearing the top of the lane and mounted a five wide bid into the stretch, closed well inside of the furlong marker, overtook PRETTY THIRSTY in deep stretch and edged away in the final strides. PRETTY THIRSTY was hustled at the break and dictated terms to the turn, set decent fractions while pressured to the quarter marker, shook free and drew to a clear lead at mid-stretch, kept to task to the sixteenth-marker, was overtaken by the winner in deep stretch and just held for second at the finish. MATCHLESS stalked the decent early pace while outside of rivals, advanced three wide on the turn, lost position nearing the furlong marker, re-rallied in deep stretch but could not muster the needed late response and just missed for second, while holding safely for third. MARY WALKER chased from the inside, ran evenly to the furlong pole and lacked a late rally. CONQUEST ROCKS was forwardly placed in the early stages, pressed the decent pace to the quarter marker, lost ground to PRETTY THIRSTY at mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Tom's Style
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,roused 5wide into stretch,closed well,edged away late

ENTRY.NAME: Pretty Thirsty
ENTRY.OWNER: Creel Allen Wedge Stephanie and Weiss Lisa

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMART KITTEN broke alertly and established the early lead, set moderate fractions into the backstretch run then was well rated to the far turn, came under pressure at the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong pole, kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker and was hand urged to the finish. LOOKIN AT SWEETIE was unhurried in the early going, raced three wide into the far turn then slipped inside approaching the top of the lane, was not able to impact the winner in deep stretch but closed with good late interest and was up for second. GET MY POINT was floated out a bit entering the first turn, tracked the modest fractions through the backstretch run, advanced three wide nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace with SMART KITTEN in the stretch run and just missed for second at the finish, while clear of the rest for third. RAUCOUS TIZZY was floated out a bit along the first turn, recovered to attend to the moderate pace through the backstretch run, confronted SMART KITTEN at the quarter marker, was turned away in that effort in upper stretch and gave way in the final furlong. ADJUST THE HEAT was prominent into the first turn, was a bit keen and floated out rivals in the early stages, tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run, lost position while two wide on the second turn, raced four wide into the stretch and tired in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Adjust the Heat
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Melinda Gioiello Vito A Lafever Bennie D and Russo Vito

ENTRY.NAME: Raucous Tizzy
ENTRY.OWNER: Edwards Roberta Morrow Nina and Watchorn Ron

ENTRY.NAME: Lookin At Sweetie
ENTRY.OWNER: George and Martha Schwary Racing LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 93. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over S ince January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WORTHY OF MAGIC broke alertly and assumed command heading to the first turn, set modest fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, drew to a clear lead approaching the far turn, was asked for more heading into the lane, held foes at bay to mid-stretch and kept to task under a drive to prevail. NAUGHTY NADINE (GB) took back off of the moderate early pace, maintained position while outside of rivals on the backstretch run, gained ground three wide on the far turn, was not able to make headway on WORTHY OF MAGIC in the stretch and held clearly at the end for second. SHEZARUNAWAY was unhurried in the early running, gained ground on the far turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong pole, could not muster the needed late response and held safely for third. KOKO'S MOM stalked the moderate pace, raced two wide to the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive. SEEMS LOGICAL was forwardly placed into the first turn, contested the moderate early pace then ceded the lead to WORTHY OF MAGIC heading into the backstretch run, tracked that rival through modest fractions to the far turn, lost position nearing the quarter marker and gave way in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Charles, Ronald L. and Gordon, Samuel

ENTRY.OWNER: Harris Farms Inc and Rowe Donna
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up early,tracked pace,inside,gave way stretch

ENTRY.OWNER: Clark Parker and William Burke Equine LLC

ENTRY.OWNER: Morrow Nina Warner Andrea and Watchorn Ron

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZAFFERANA was allowed to settle in the early stages, loomed along the turn, angled four wide into the stretch, advanced at mid-stretch, encountered a stubborn rival in BIG STRIKE in the final stages, made a determined late surge under firm handling and prevailed in the final strides. BIG STRIKE showed good early speed and set a quick pace heading to the turn, dueled with DAREDEVIL PRINCESS to the quarter marker, shook free of that rival in upper stretch and drew to a clear lead approaching the furlong grounds, held foes at bay to the sixteenth-marker, battled stubbornly against the winner in deep stretch but was caught by ZAFFERANA and held safely for second. CRY ME A RUNNER chased the decent early pace, raced three wide into the stretch, gained ground nearing the furlong pole, was not able to keep pace with the top two in deep stretch and was well clear in the end for third. DAREDEVIL PRINCESS was prominent in the early running, pressed the decent pace to the turn, dueled with BIG STRIKE to the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. TIGERIZE took back off of the decent early pace, raced three wide to the quarter marker, did not threaten in the stretch run and passed a tired rival in the final stages. ABBEY OOPS rushed up in the opening stages and chased the decent pace to the turn, saved ground on the turn while in pursuit and tired in the stretch drive. ROUSING STAR hopped at the start and was off slowly, lacked early speed and trailed into the turn, raced three wide into the stretch and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Rousing Star
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start,off slowly,no speed,3wide into stretch,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Big Strike
ENTRY.OWNER: Brewer Racing Stable and Dutko Mitchell
ENTRY.COMMENT: good early speed,shook free 3/16,battled stubbornly late,caught

ENTRY.NAME: Tigerize
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,3wide turn,no threat,passed tired rival late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 1M All Weather Track CR: 91. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEX HANLEY allowed to settle while never far back, was roused three wide nearing the top of the lane, was full of run at mid-stretch, was kept to steady urging to deep stretch, took command inside of the sixteenth-marker and kicked clear in the final stages. THANKS MAGGIO (ARG) was prominent into the first turn, tracked the early pace then advanced to press the pace into the second turn, battled with STORMIN GALILEO in upper stretch and took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, could not match strides with TEX HANLEY in the late stages and held well in deep stretch to secure second. STORMIN GALILEO broke alertly, showed early speed and set the pace into the backstretch run, set pressured fractions to the quarter marker, battled with THANKS MAGGIO to the furlong marker, could not keep pace with TEX HANLEY in the final furlong, weakened in deep stretch and was outfinished for second, while holding at the end for third. ZIPPY BABY settled just off of the early pace, improved position along the backstretch run, was well placed while saving ground nearing the quarter marker, lost ground approaching the top of the stretch, re-rallied in the drive but could not muster the needed late response and missed for the minor awards. RULER OF ANGELS settled off of the moderate early pace, chased between runners through the backstretch run, came two wide between rivals into the far turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker while still within aim and gave way in the late stages. HICKORY WIND stalked the moderate early pace while outside of rivals, raced three wide into the backstretch run, improved position nearing the second turn, lost ground three deep at the quarter marker, swung four wide into the stretch and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Thanks Maggio (ARG)
ENTRY.OWNER: Baldwin Ronald Hilding Ray Psarras Andreas and Wakefield Ed

ENTRY.NAME: Ruler of Angels
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,chased 2wide btwn 2nd turn,evenly to 1/8,gave way late

ENTRY.NAME: Tex Hanley
ENTRY.COMMENT: never far back,roused 3wide into stretch,full of run,drove clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 6F All Weather Track CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5 0,000 (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered For The Optional Claimi ng Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IDAHO ONCE broke alertly and sped to the early lead, was engaged by RACHEL'S COACH in the first furlong and dueled through fast fractions with that rival to the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch, drove to a clear lead at the furlong pole, kept to task in deep stretch while on the left lead and remained clear to the wire. RODRIGOKNOWS was forwardly placed in the early stages then took back to track the fast pace, tracked two wide to the quarter marker, mounted a three wide rally into the stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker, could not impact the winner in the final stages and ran on to secure second. CHUCKANUT BAY was unhurried in the early going, raced two wide to the quarter marker, improved position at mid-stretch, found his best stride late, closed well in deep stretch and just missed for second, while securing third in the final strides. RACHEL'S COACH was sent in the first furlong and contested the fast early pace, dueled with IDAHO ONCE to the quarter pole, could not match strides with that foe nearing the furlong marker, weakened in the final stages while on the left lead and was outfinished for the minor awards. TALK ABOUT AUTISM chased the fast early pace, lost ground while outside of rivals on the turn, came four wide into the stretch, offered a mild bid in the final furlong but could not muster the needed response. SAXON SAGA was shuffled back at the start and was off a step slowly, chased from the second flight, saved ground to the top of the lane and did not threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Rodrigoknows
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,3wide into stretch,rallied,finished well,up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Talk About Autism
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace,4wide into stretch,mild late bid,needed more

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 77. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when det ermining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLACK ZABAT broke sharply and went straight to the lead, held sway through the turn while always traveling well, responded when asked at the three-sixteenths maker and drew away to an impressive score. A ROUSING BABE got away well but raced near the back of the pack and four wide to the turn, made a sweeping bid through the turn while still wide, sustained the run though the stretch and was best of the rest. SONOMA DREAMING broke in and made light contact with BLACKENED, was a little hard to place in the run down the backstretch, made a strong bid from the nine-sixteenths pole racing in the three path, entered the stretch in second position while racing on the left lead, had some trouble getting straight down the lane and was passed late for the place. DANZIGS STAR STORM reserved near the pack of the pack early, moved up into contention racing in the two path on the turn, tipped out for room at the top of the stretch and ran on well enough to pass a few in the late stages. BLACKENED broke in, bumped with YODERANDO at the break, worked over to the rail and tracked the pacesetter to the turn, got a good inside trip into the stretch, steadied approaching the three furlong marker, was unable to find another gear when needed and finished one-paced to the wire while holding position. BOB'S VAI broke well and settled into a stalking position just behind and to the outside of BLACK ZABAT to the turn, remained a looming threat to the top of the stretch then weakened in the final furlong. OTTER POP broke well but was outrun for the lead, settled mid-pack early, struggled to keep up through the turn and was never a threat. YODERANDO veered out at the start making contact with BLACKENED, then steadied after the break when that same rival too the path, lost momentum then gathered up, kept to the outside and regained some momentum going into the turn, remained wide through the turn and swung six wide into the stretch but was unable to improve position.

ENTRY.OWNER: Thomas A Farrell Bypass Trust and MJVET Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, settled mid-pack, struggled turn, never a threat

ENTRY.NAME: Black Zabat
ENTRY.COMMENT: zipped to lead, held sway turn, responded 3/16, drew off
